Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of possess Methamphetamine with intent to deliver.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.
The defendant has credit for 157 days.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination.
Minutes.
